<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Unpacking Polygon Interoperability Cross-Chain Transactions</h2>



<p>At its core, Polygon achieves cross-chain interoperability through its Polygon Bridge, which acts as a secure and efficient bridge between Ethereum and the Polygon network. </p>



<p>By utilizing a combination of decentralized validators and a custom checkpointing mechanism, Polygon ensures the secure transfer of assets between different blockchains.</p>



<p>This process involves locking assets on one blockchain, validating the transaction, and minting equivalent assets on the target blockchain.</p>



<p>Additionally, Polygon&#8217;s interoperability is bolstered by its support for multiple standards such as ERC-20 and ERC-721, enabling a wide range of assets to be seamlessly transferred across chains.</p>



<p>Understanding these mechanisms is crucial for grasping the intricate workings of Polygon&#8217;s cross-chain interoperability.</p>



<p>To understand the latest on Polygon Interoperability, read our update in <a href="https://securenest.org/learn/polygon-interoperability-api-integration">Polygon Interoperability API Integration</a>.</p>



