<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Addressing Risks and Security in Interoperable Transactions</h3>



<p>Polygon leverages advanced cryptographic techniques such as multi-signature schemes and threshold signatures to secure cross-chain transactions. </p>



<p>These mechanisms require multiple cryptographic keys to authorize a transaction, thereby reducing the risk of a single point of failure.</p>



<p>Additionally, Polygon utilizes secure multi-party computation (MPC) to enable privacy-preserving cross-chain transactions. MPC ensures that no single party has access to the complete private data, enhancing the confidentiality of transactions.</p>



<p>Furthermore, Polygon&#8217;s interoperability protocol integrates with reputable security oracles to validate and verify cross-chain transactions, adding an extra layer of security.</p>



